            "notes": [
                {
                    "category": "summary",
                    "text": "NVIDIA GeForce Now for Android contains a vulnerability in the game launcher component, where a malicious application on the same device can process the implicit intent meant for the streamer component. A successful exploit of this vulnerability may lead to limited information disclosure, denial of service, and code execution.<br/>*CWE Info*<b>Use of Implicit Intent for Sensitive Communication</b><hr/>The Android application uses an implicit intent for transmitting sensitive data to other applications.<br/>************************",
